
[1]seriousness

   SE'RIOUSNESS, n.

   1. Gravity of manner or of mind; solemnity. He spoke with great
   serioulness, or with an air of seriousness.

   2. Earnest attention, particularly to religious concerns

   That spirit of religion and seriousness vanished all at once.
   Atterbury.
